    "created_at": "2020-04-14T15:57:07Z",
    "updated_at": "2020-04-14T15:57:40Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "> Should we consider adding an assignments stream? Validators can subscribe to a given stream for assignments and in the event of a reorg then the beacon node sends new assignments immediately rather than the start of each epoch.\r\n\r\nI think that is a great idea. \r\nThe least resistant path is just to have validators check their duties every slot to ensure that chain reorgs are recognized, although I don't have much concrete data to analysis how expensive that is.\r\nGiven this is higher priority after seeing many att sig fails to verify, there's two options:\r\n1.) Implement duties streaming\r\n\r\n2.) Implement validators polling duty every slot and gated behind a feature flag, then implement duties streaming. Both implementations can happen in parrell.\r\n\r\nWould you prefer 2 over 1?  @prestonvanloon ",
